.SH "NAME"
devm_iio_trigger_register \- Resource\-managed \fBiio_trigger_register\fR
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ devm_iio_trigger_register('u
.BI "int devm_iio_trigger_register(struct\ device\ *\ " "dev" ", struct\ iio_trigger\ *\ " "trig_info" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
device this trigger was allocated for
.RE
.PP
\fItrig_info\fR
.RS 4
trigger to register
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Managed
\fBiio_trigger_register\fR\&. The IIO trigger registered with this function is automatically unregistered on driver detach\&. This function calls
\fBiio_trigger_register\fR
internally\&. Refer to that function for more information\&.
.PP
If an iio_trigger registered with this function needs to be unregistered separately,
\fBdevm_iio_trigger_unregister\fR
must be used\&.
.SH "RETURN"
.PP
0 on success, negative error number on failure\&.
